  "prompt": "Which is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Upson County GA?",
  "response": "While I can't provide real-time specific recommendations or details about individual facilities, I can suggest a few ways to find suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab centers near Upson County, GA:\n\n1. **Online Directories**: Websites like SAMHSA's Treatment Locator (https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/) offer a comprehensive list of treatment facilities by state and zip code.\n\n2. **Local Health Departments**: Contacting your local health department or community health center can provide information about available resources in Upson County and surrounding areas.\n\n3. **Insurance Provider**: If you have health insurance, check with your provider for a list of covered rehab facilities.\n\n4. **Referrals**: Speak with healthcare providers or counselors who can recommend reputable rehab centers based on your needs.\n\n5. **Support Groups**: Organizations like Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) or Narcotics Anonymous (NA) often have local connections and can suggest rehab centers.\n\n6. **Online Reviews and Ratings**: Platforms like Google, Yelp, or specialized rehab review sites can provide insights and feedback from former patients.\n\nMake sure to consider the specific needs of the individual seeking treatment when looking for a facility, such as the type of addiction, co-occurring disorders, length of stay, and type of treatment offered.",
